mation libraries, current page architecture, and whether framer-motion or motion/react is installed. Confirm whether any Aceternity UI components already exist; do not install anything. Check that there is no app/[...slug]/page.tsx and no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx. Search for PublicRoutePage imports and slug catch-all references. Check whether the landing page has all required homepage sections: Hero, Enterprise Quick Search, Garage Foundry Factory journey, What We Build, Interactive Experience, Global Presence, Client Success, Live Dashboard, Latest Research, Contact, Footer. Check whether all public pages are explicit App Router pages. Check whether the Blueprint scoring formula exists and whether the banking test case can return 87/100. Produce a gap list only. Do not edit files. Final response must include files inspected, missing items, route gaps, homepage gaps, design-system observations, animation-library availability, and recommended next task.\"\n./automation/tasks.json:100:    \"title\": \"Verify and fix Blueprint Generator scoring\",\n./automation/tasks.json:200:    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /platforms/blueprint, /platforms/marketplace, and /platforms/control-center as premium enterprise product pages. Do not touch landing page. Blueprint page: explain enterprise AI blueprints, readiness scoring, solution recommendations, expected impact, 90-day roadmap, and link to /build/blueprint. Marketplace page: curated agent patterns and accelerators, no fake purchasable products or pricing. Control Center page: monitor AI programs, agent health, spend, adoption, governance, delivery operations, but no fake live metrics. Use product-grade hero visuals, tabs, carousels, dashboard-style preview panels without fake numbers, architecture diagrams, and CTAs. Make each page unique while sharing platform family design. Use Framer Motion and local Aceternity-inspired effects if available. Run lint/build.\"\n./automation/tasks.json:232:    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /build and all Build With GFF subpages into polished self-service enterprise tool pages. Pages: /build, /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Do not touch landing page. Design mood: interactive, guided journey, conversion-focused, enterprise self-service. /build should show the journey: Visitor, AI Assessment, Blueprint, Workshop, Proposal, Contract, Delivery, Operate, Expand. /build/talk should feel like AI challenge intake with challenge description, industry, company size, frontend-only preview outputs Proposal, Squad, Timeline. /build/blueprint should be a polished wizard using the scoring rules. /build/assessment should feel like readiness diagnostic. /build/roi should feel like executive calculator with illustrative estimates only. /build/sandbox should feel like secure preview environment with no real runtime. /build/proposal should feel like proposal studio with PPT/PDF/SOW export cards as frontend preview only. /build/marketplace and /build/foundry-studio should be premium previews. Use forms, tabs, stepped flows, carousels, result panels, Framer Motion if available, Aceternity-inspired UI effects locally. No real API calls, no fake exports, no fake OTP. Run lint/build.\"\n","success":true},{"query":"grep -rn --exclude-dir=node_modules --exclude-dir=.next \"banking\" . || true","result":"./tsconfig.tsbuildinfo:1:{\"fileNames\":[\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es5.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2015.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2016.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2017.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2018.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2019.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2020.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2021.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2022.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2023.d.ts\",\"./node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.es2024.d.ts\",\"./